1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,000
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,000
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:03,000
(Generative AI technology
was used in certain scenes.)

4
00:00:04,433 --> 00:00:08,300
Your dad and I
were prison buddies 25 years ago.

5
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:12,200
We shared the same cell for five years.

6
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:17,333
I'll report you right away,
so you'd better be ready.

7
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:18,533
Report me?

8
00:00:22,986 --> 00:00:24,619
Listen, young lady.

9
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,266
Your dad's a murderer.

10
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:30,766
He killed someone.

11
00:00:34,906 --> 00:00:37,113
What? You don't believe me?

12
00:00:37,773 --> 00:00:41,219
No.
My dad would never do something like that.

13
00:00:41,940 --> 00:00:45,173
If you don't believe me,
ask your dad yourself.

14
00:00:45,673 --> 00:00:47,533
Ask him who 4885 is.

15
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,946
- Then you'll have your answer.
- Wait.

16
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:55,086
Take your dirty threats up with me.

17
00:00:55,486 --> 00:00:57,473
- What?
- Let's make a deal.

18
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,900
But first, show me solid proof.

19
00:01:01,993 --> 00:01:03,772
Then we'll negotiate.

20
00:01:05,673 --> 00:01:07,319
You're quite a bold young lady.

21
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:10,620
You're the one who has to find the proof.

22
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:13,219
Three days again.

23
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:16,999
Ask your dad yourself,
or find out on your own.

24
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:21,486
Once you've confirmed it's true,
get the money ready and call me.

25
00:01:21,979 --> 00:01:22,979
One week.

26
00:01:23,946 --> 00:01:26,259
I'll need that much time
to find the proof myself...

27
00:01:26,819 --> 00:01:28,019
and come up with the money.

28
00:01:28,966 --> 00:01:29,966
But in return,

29
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:33,540
promise me
you'll never contact my dad again.

30
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:38,279
Keep that promise, and I'll give you two.

31
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:41,206
What? Two?

32
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:49,173
Looks like 4885 raised
quite a devoted daughter. Fine.

33
00:01:50,753 --> 00:01:53,572
But if you break your promise,

34
00:01:53,573 --> 00:01:54,913
you know what'll happen, right?

35
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,686
Not just your dad,

36
00:01:58,386 --> 00:02:01,686
I'll take you both down in one shot.

37
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:19,646
Your dad and I
were prison buddies 25 years ago.

38
00:02:20,573 --> 00:02:22,773
We shared the same cell for five years.

39
00:02:23,973 --> 00:02:26,573
I told you.

40
00:02:27,179 --> 00:02:30,939
He was in Poland when Kangsu Construction
established its Eastern European branch.

41
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:37,253
The Eastern European branch 25 years ago?

42
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:50,533
(Permanent Archive 1996-2000)

43
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:54,900
(History of Overseas Expansion)

44
00:02:59,133 --> 00:03:00,400
(2000,
Eastern European Branch Established)

45
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,133
(Early Branch Members)

46
00:03:06,153 --> 00:03:07,726
Dad's name isn't here.

47
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:15,033
Why is everything so quiet?

48
00:03:15,673 --> 00:03:18,966
Did Mother collapse after arguing
with Kang Yeon Ja?

49
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:23,493
She looked absolutely furious
at Mother earlier.

50
00:03:23,900 --> 00:03:26,733
Yeah. That was nothing like...

51
00:03:26,733 --> 00:03:30,353
one of those
tearful mother-daughter reunions.

52
00:03:30,586 --> 00:03:33,306
Even if Mother and Father both want to,
it won't be easy to add her...

53
00:03:33,746 --> 00:03:35,512
to the family registry
if she refuses, right?

54
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,460
I guess so.

55
00:03:38,093 --> 00:03:39,886
Not if she doesn't want to.

56
00:03:41,099 --> 00:03:42,659
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

57
00:03:45,779 --> 00:03:46,779
Got it.

58
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:48,933
From now on, our job...

59
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:51,313
Is to make sure Kang Yeon Ja's name...

60
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:53,072
never gets added
to Father's family registry.

61
00:03:57,280 --> 00:04:01,153
Hey, it's the weekend.
Where are you going?

62
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:04,206
The competition's just around the corner.
I need to get to the office and work.

63
00:04:04,726 --> 00:04:07,386
Come with me. We need to talk.

64
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:13,139
Have a good talk, you guys!

65
00:04:14,533 --> 00:04:17,760
Eun Su Jeong,
they say even a tiger survives...

66
00:04:17,886 --> 00:04:20,213
if it keeps its wits about it
in a fox's den.

67
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,733
Stay sharp.

68
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:25,219
The real game starts now.

69
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,640
You finally get the situation now,
don't you?

70
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:31,926
Now you know why
I told you not to lose this competition.

71
00:04:32,026 --> 00:04:35,532
What does Grandma's daughter showing up
have to do with the competition?

72
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:37,618
Why are you so slow?

73
00:04:37,619 --> 00:04:40,791
Listen. Grandma's daughter showing up...

74
00:04:40,792 --> 00:04:44,660
means your father
has a powerful new rival.

75
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:49,326
Do you think half of Grandpa's shares
will just go to Grandma?

76
00:04:50,126 --> 00:04:51,780
If you lose this competition,

77
00:04:52,093 --> 00:04:54,499
Grandpa's remaining shares
will go to Gyeol,

78
00:04:54,792 --> 00:04:57,139
and then Grandma and her daughter...

79
00:04:57,139 --> 00:04:59,139
will swallow up the rest.

80
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:02,852
Then we'll be finished.

81
00:05:02,853 --> 00:05:04,053
Finished. Gone.

82
00:05:05,466 --> 00:05:08,479
I think I've already given you
several yellow cards.

83
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,699
You are racing against us right now, Dad.

84
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,846
Why do you keep forgetting that?

85
00:05:14,233 --> 00:05:15,233
What?

86
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:19,873
Right. I'm competing against my sons too.

87
00:05:21,133 --> 00:05:22,226
I'll get going now.

88
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:27,679
Wait a minute.

89
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:31,773
At this rate, I might lose to Min Ho too.

90
00:05:32,139 --> 00:05:33,139
I need to get my head straight.

91
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:49,212
Gyeol, if Eun Ae is there with you,

92
00:05:49,213 --> 00:05:50,419
could you put her on?

93
00:05:51,386 --> 00:05:54,286
No, just give me her number.

94
00:05:55,073 --> 00:05:56,712
There's something I want to tell her.

95
00:05:57,786 --> 00:05:59,119
Please do that for me.

96
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:08,959
Eun Ae.

97
00:06:09,099 --> 00:06:11,766
Hello, Grandma. Did you sleep well?

98
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:13,813
I did.

99
00:06:14,726 --> 00:06:16,373
Your mom's having a hard time, isn't she?

100
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,539
Please don't worry too much.

101
00:06:18,966 --> 00:06:21,019
She just needs time.

102
00:06:22,766 --> 00:06:24,793
You don't have to be so formal anymore.

103
00:06:25,133 --> 00:06:26,533
I'm your granddaughter too.

104
00:06:27,073 --> 00:06:28,346
All right.

105
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:33,073
Eun Ae, stop by when you have time.

106
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,753
There's so much I'd like to ask you.

107
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:41,400
I will. I'll come see you
as soon as this competition is over.

108
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,960
Right.
I'll send you a few pictures of Mom.

109
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:46,893
I thought you'd like to see them.

110
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:51,779
Thank you so much. I'll be waiting.

111
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:58,845
You already look so much better...

112
00:06:58,846 --> 00:07:01,546
after talking to your granddaughter.

113
00:07:02,140 --> 00:07:03,140
Yes.

114
00:07:04,873 --> 00:07:07,532
Yeon Sun must be going through hell
right now.

115
00:07:21,933 --> 00:07:22,986
My goodness.

116
00:07:24,293 --> 00:07:26,759
Maybe life isn't so unfair after all.

117
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:31,940
Seeing that Yeon Sun
found a good husband...

118
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:35,453
and built such a happy family...

119
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:39,566
You're right.
Someone was looking out for her.

120
00:07:41,459 --> 00:07:43,172
She has three children.

121
00:07:48,386 --> 00:07:51,326
I shouldn't ask for anything more.

122
00:07:52,866 --> 00:07:56,126
Just seeing Yeon Sun
living such a happy life...

123
00:07:57,833 --> 00:07:59,492
has left me with no regrets.

124
00:08:08,673 --> 00:08:10,300
That's too heavy, Mother. I'll do it.

125
00:08:11,559 --> 00:08:12,753
I just need to put it in the fridge,
right?

126
00:08:17,686 --> 00:08:20,193
I wasn't joking
when I told you to move out.

127
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:22,140
You understand what I said, right?

128
00:08:22,899 --> 00:08:24,846
Yes. I understand.

129
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,132
Team Manager, we don't have time for this.

130
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:28,133
We need to get back to work.

131
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,265
Mom, we're heading to the office. Come on.

132
00:08:30,266 --> 00:08:31,619
We'll be off now.

133
00:08:50,306 --> 00:08:51,740
Don't just stand there.

134
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:54,280
Take Eun Hyeong and Bit Na
out for some fresh air.

135
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:56,379
I'm going to do some deep cleaning.

136
00:08:56,626 --> 00:08:59,592
The whole family
does the deep cleaning together.

137
00:09:00,386 --> 00:09:02,599
Let's finish this first,
then go for a walk together.

138
00:09:02,799 --> 00:09:04,266
Maybe getting some fresh air...

139
00:09:04,266 --> 00:09:05,326
Honey.

140
00:09:06,933 --> 00:09:09,793
All right. I'll go out.

141
00:09:10,206 --> 00:09:12,873
We'll do the deep cleaning tomorrow, okay?

142
00:09:24,453 --> 00:09:25,453
This feels great.

143
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:27,266
It really does.

144
00:09:27,266 --> 00:09:29,746
Dad's all better now.
Bit Na has healing hands!

145
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:33,112
Come here. Up you go.

146
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,479
Did it hurt a lot?

147
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:39,226
No. I wasn't hurting at all.

148
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:40,740
If you weren't hurting,

149
00:09:40,740 --> 00:09:44,260
then why do you always groan
in your sleep?

150
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,506
Me? Maybe you were dreaming.

151
00:09:48,646 --> 00:09:50,619
Dad, I'm seven years old.

152
00:09:50,619 --> 00:09:51,819
I know everything.

153
00:09:52,439 --> 00:09:56,739
I know you're working so hard
because you want to get me a pretty room.

154
00:09:58,352 --> 00:10:01,520
I'm sorry your room disappeared
all of a sudden,

155
00:10:02,046 --> 00:10:04,633
and you've had to sleep
in different rooms.

156
00:10:05,020 --> 00:10:08,140
It's okay.
Everyone in our family loves me.

157
00:10:08,913 --> 00:10:09,913
Including Auntie Cho Rong.

158
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:13,346
My Bit Na is so mature.

159
00:10:14,086 --> 00:10:16,486
How can a seven-year-old be this mature?

160
00:10:16,926 --> 00:10:20,272
So you don't have to work so hard...

161
00:10:20,273 --> 00:10:21,613
just to get me a pretty room.

162
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:24,285
More than a pretty room,

163
00:10:24,286 --> 00:10:26,246
I'd rather have a healthy dad.

164
00:10:27,639 --> 00:10:28,739
Thank you, Bit Na.

165
00:10:29,306 --> 00:10:33,373
It's just that I've only ever studied.
Physical work is new to me.

166
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,293
I'll get used to it soon,
so don't worry, okay?

167
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:41,493
What's wrong?
Something's bothering you, isn't it?

168
00:10:51,433 --> 00:10:52,433
What's this?

169
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,233
(Mom Participation Day Notice)

170
00:10:54,359 --> 00:10:55,972
Mom Participation Day?

171
00:10:57,179 --> 00:10:59,499
Mom can't come that day, can she?

172
00:11:00,906 --> 00:11:02,099
It's next week.

173
00:11:03,133 --> 00:11:05,526
I don't really know Mom's flight schedule,

174
00:11:06,059 --> 00:11:07,966
so I can't give you a definite answer.

175
00:11:09,119 --> 00:11:11,659
What if Grandma goes instead?

176
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,279
Grandma?

177
00:11:13,559 --> 00:11:16,059
Everyone else's mom will be there, though.

178
00:11:16,693 --> 00:11:19,706
I'll text Mom first
and ask if she can come.

179
00:11:20,266 --> 00:11:24,719
Okay. If she can't, I'll go with Grandma.

180
00:11:25,426 --> 00:11:27,333
Sounds good.

181
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,153
Bit Na.

182
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,012
Want to go for a walk
with Dad and Grandpa?

183
00:11:34,013 --> 00:11:35,386
Okay, Grandpa.

184
00:11:35,953 --> 00:11:37,526
How's Mom doing?

185
00:11:40,146 --> 00:11:43,719
There she goes again,
pushing herself too hard.

186
00:11:45,072 --> 00:11:46,139
What should we do about Mom?

187
00:11:50,686 --> 00:11:51,906
Where did she go?

188
00:12:07,013 --> 00:12:08,206
Hello, Chief.

189
00:12:08,466 --> 00:12:10,499
Hello. Looks like
you gave up your day off too, Team Two.

190
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:14,113
I heard about Grandma.

191
00:12:14,633 --> 00:12:16,519
Yes. You must've been shocked.

192
00:12:17,086 --> 00:12:18,472
I really was.

193
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:22,559
If your mother is my grandma's daughter,
then she's my dad's sister.

194
00:12:22,946 --> 00:12:24,926
Then she'd be my aunt.

195
00:12:25,186 --> 00:12:28,866
Ms. Cho, could you send me
the final revised Joy file?

196
00:12:29,013 --> 00:12:30,433
Sure.

197
00:12:30,433 --> 00:12:33,979
Then does that make you and me cousins?

198
00:12:34,346 --> 00:12:35,346
Chief.

199
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,699
Is Team One all set for the competition?

200
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:40,986
Fine. I'm off.

201
00:12:42,033 --> 00:12:45,353
Right. When Manager Seo comes,
tell her to stop by my office.

202
00:12:45,593 --> 00:12:46,993
I think she left her phone behind.

203
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:48,633
Yes, Chief.

204
00:12:50,879 --> 00:12:54,593
Team Manager,
aren't you a little too blunt with him?

205
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,000
Too blunt?

206
00:12:57,473 --> 00:13:01,493
Sometimes, you seem a little too harsh.

207
00:13:02,226 --> 00:13:04,426
Chief Ko is actually a really nice person.

208
00:13:05,166 --> 00:13:07,226
If my little brother said that to me,
I'd...

209
00:13:10,386 --> 00:13:11,853
I'll get back to work.

210
00:13:14,179 --> 00:13:16,579
Let's finish the final review by today,
okay?

211
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:17,700
Yes, sir.

212
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:20,633
What did you say?

213
00:13:21,406 --> 00:13:25,206
You think the heroine, Ban Do Yeon,
is too violent?

214
00:13:25,206 --> 00:13:27,479
It's not just my opinion.

215
00:13:27,481 --> 00:13:30,358
I've seen readers complain about it
in the reviews too.

216
00:13:30,359 --> 00:13:34,019
Listen, Ban Do Yeon has always been
that kind of character.

217
00:13:34,219 --> 00:13:36,758
She can't stand injustice
or people who bully the weak.

218
00:13:36,759 --> 00:13:38,893
She never tolerates people
who abuse their power.

219
00:13:38,893 --> 00:13:40,146
That's true, but...

220
00:13:41,066 --> 00:13:43,425
Then what about the way she yells
at the intern, Yu Jin Seok,

221
00:13:43,432 --> 00:13:45,051
and keeps smacking him around?

222
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,619
Did he commit some kind of injustice...

223
00:13:47,620 --> 00:13:49,453
or abuse his power?

224
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,846
He's incompetent.

225
00:13:52,586 --> 00:13:56,426
He's an intern who can't even
operate an Ambu bag properly.

226
00:13:56,633 --> 00:13:58,766
He wants to be a doctor,
yet he trembles...

227
00:13:58,993 --> 00:14:01,873
at the sight of a needle
in an ER where lives are on the line.

228
00:14:02,439 --> 00:14:05,026
That's why she keeps chewing him out.

229
00:14:05,892 --> 00:14:09,146
You know, that actually makes sense.

230
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:11,039
Then that's it for today's meeting.

231
00:14:12,946 --> 00:14:15,392
By the way,

232
00:14:15,793 --> 00:14:18,266
has Oh Hye Ji contacted you
since your Two-Two Day?

233
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,300
No.

234
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:23,479
And it wasn't a Two-Two Day.

235
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:25,400
It was all just a misunderstanding.

236
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:26,646
Who even cares?

237
00:14:35,299 --> 00:14:36,352
Yu Jin Seok!

238
00:14:39,540 --> 00:14:40,540
Get over here.

239
00:14:41,126 --> 00:14:43,779
Come here while I'm asking nicely. Now!

240
00:14:50,526 --> 00:14:51,526
Wait.

241
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:55,033
These punks are saying...

242
00:14:55,433 --> 00:14:57,873
"Dorodorthy should quit."

243
00:14:58,553 --> 00:14:59,706
"Did you write it with your feet?"

244
00:15:00,339 --> 00:15:02,239
"Can't stand this violent writer."

245
00:15:03,060 --> 00:15:05,266
You've got to be kidding me.

246
00:15:06,786 --> 00:15:08,653
Hey, you think
you can just say whatever you want?

247
00:15:08,653 --> 00:15:09,920
(ER King)

248
00:15:10,113 --> 00:15:13,146
Do you have any idea
how deep the writer's artistic vision is?

249
00:15:13,693 --> 00:15:16,693
Who am I? I'm a devoted reader.
A true fan!

250
00:15:17,819 --> 00:15:20,213
You kids should just stay out of it.

251
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:24,026
What? You want to settle this?

252
00:15:24,381 --> 00:15:25,973
Great. I'd love to.

253
00:15:25,973 --> 00:15:29,319
Hey, let's meet. Right now!

254
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:34,726
A real-life showdown? Fine. Let's do it.

255
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:37,799
Just you wait.

256
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:39,899
You're all dead.

257
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,979
Where did he go? He was just here.

258
00:15:58,433 --> 00:16:01,726
Did he actually go fight someone
over a comment war?

259
00:16:05,013 --> 00:16:06,246
Are you ER King?

260
00:16:06,554 --> 00:16:09,639
What? No, I'm not.

261
00:16:09,639 --> 00:16:12,580
I'm Napkin Genius.

262
00:16:12,580 --> 00:16:14,306
Wait. Napkin Genius?

263
00:16:14,633 --> 00:16:17,586
You're the guy who picked a fight
with me yesterday, aren't you?

264
00:16:18,133 --> 00:16:21,733
So you changed your username
and trashed us...

265
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:24,033
in the comments?

266
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:27,306
No. There's no way.

267
00:16:28,639 --> 00:16:30,139
I gave it some thought,

268
00:16:30,319 --> 00:16:32,506
and my name is Bung Wu.

269
00:16:33,299 --> 00:16:34,299
Well then.

270
00:16:36,679 --> 00:16:40,272
Not so fast. Weren't you the one
who wanted to meet right away?

271
00:16:44,046 --> 00:16:46,439
Hey, you punks!

272
00:16:53,606 --> 00:16:54,713
Will you stop it already?

273
00:16:55,879 --> 00:16:56,879
Ms. Cho.

274
00:16:57,259 --> 00:16:59,852
And who are you? His girlfriend?

275
00:16:59,853 --> 00:17:02,246
Yeah!
So what are you going to do about it?

276
00:17:03,060 --> 00:17:05,251
What's wrong with you?
What if you get hurt?

277
00:17:05,251 --> 00:17:06,518
Come on. Let's go.

278
00:17:07,499 --> 00:17:09,298
Move while I'm asking nicely.

279
00:17:09,299 --> 00:17:11,799
No, I don't think I will.

280
00:17:13,426 --> 00:17:15,126
Come on.

281
00:17:15,859 --> 00:17:17,352
You basement-dwelling losers!

282
00:17:17,353 --> 00:17:19,466
What? Basement-dwelling losers?

283
00:17:19,633 --> 00:17:21,346
You want to die?

284
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:24,739
Even so, this isn't right.

285
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:26,733
How dare you touch my girlfriend?

286
00:17:28,726 --> 00:17:31,426
Fine. You want to die together?

287
00:17:31,786 --> 00:17:33,893
Get them, guys!

288
00:17:34,026 --> 00:17:35,446
Wait!

289
00:17:36,093 --> 00:17:38,493
Before we really get started,
we'll warm up first.

290
00:17:39,059 --> 00:17:40,359
Sure. Go ahead.

291
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:43,580
Remember our Shaolin martial arts?

292
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:47,200
- Yes.
- We'll throw them off first.

293
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:49,726
Then move when I give the signal, okay?

294
00:17:50,006 --> 00:17:51,006
Okay.

295
00:17:54,613 --> 00:17:56,113
Hi-ya!

296
00:18:03,733 --> 00:18:05,213
- Now!
- Run!

297
00:18:06,973 --> 00:18:08,226
What are you doing? Get them!

298
00:18:09,166 --> 00:18:10,166
Hey!

299
00:18:18,533 --> 00:18:20,932
What happened? Why is she still...

300
00:18:24,100 --> 00:18:26,133
Wait, she still hasn't come back?

301
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:27,960
No.

302
00:18:38,566 --> 00:18:39,912
Yes, Mother. It's me.

303
00:18:40,719 --> 00:18:42,799
Hasn't Seung Ri come home yet?

304
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:45,333
Okay.

305
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:48,533
Her bag and phone are still at the office,

306
00:18:48,533 --> 00:18:49,826
but I can't find her anywhere.

307
00:18:50,066 --> 00:18:54,032
Really? I was getting worried
since she wasn't answering her phone.

308
00:18:54,033 --> 00:18:55,446
I'll keep looking.

309
00:18:55,606 --> 00:18:57,433
Her bag's here,
so I'm sure she'll be back soon.

310
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:07,353
Where on earth did she go?

311
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:25,479
So this is what you meant
by finishing your assignment?

312
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,566
Finding the Chairman's wife's daughter?

313
00:19:29,233 --> 00:19:31,700
So how did it end? Did you find her?

314
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,540
My goodness.

315
00:19:36,233 --> 00:19:37,700
How? Who is it?

316
00:19:38,839 --> 00:19:40,019
Someone you know.

317
00:19:40,593 --> 00:19:43,779
Someone I know? Who?

318
00:19:44,533 --> 00:19:46,099
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

319
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:49,920
Manager Seo should be okay, right?

320
00:19:50,633 --> 00:19:52,946
I know. It's already past six.

321
00:19:57,673 --> 00:20:00,173
Hello, ma'am. It's been a while.

322
00:20:01,260 --> 00:20:04,873
What? Again? There's another leak?

323
00:20:06,086 --> 00:20:07,186
That's serious.

324
00:20:07,859 --> 00:20:11,599
I can't make it today,
but I'll stop by tomorrow. Bye.

325
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:13,400
Who was that?

326
00:20:14,533 --> 00:20:17,079
The lady from Maeseong Pavilion
who played Go with you.

327
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:19,259
- That lady?
- Yes.

328
00:20:19,833 --> 00:20:23,160
Things were already in bad shape then,
and now the drain's clogged again.

329
00:20:23,566 --> 00:20:26,033
The rainy season's almost here,
and the leaks are getting worse.

330
00:20:26,459 --> 00:20:29,565
I'll stop by tomorrow morning
and do some basic repairs.

331
00:20:29,566 --> 00:20:31,212
Do you have time for that?

332
00:20:31,472 --> 00:20:33,906
We start full-scale rehearsals tomorrow.

333
00:20:34,046 --> 00:20:37,399
We can stay up all night if we have to.

334
00:20:38,719 --> 00:20:40,079
Urgent matters come first.

335
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:42,086
They can't even go about
their daily lives right now.

336
00:20:42,832 --> 00:20:45,300
That's true. I'll help too.

337
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:46,833
Thank you.

338
00:20:48,313 --> 00:20:51,773
Can you drive?
I mean a car, not a scooter.

339
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,280
Yes. Why?

340
00:20:54,819 --> 00:20:56,919
I need to borrow and haul some equipment,

341
00:20:56,919 --> 00:20:58,286
and a scooter won't do.

342
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:03,133
It may have been a while, but I passed
my driving test on the first try.

343
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:06,073
- But what about the car?
- We'll rent one.

344
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:07,600
Rent one?

345
00:21:07,966 --> 00:21:10,966
Since tomorrow's Sunday,
do you want to borrow my dad's car?

346
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:14,506
Your father's car?
Would that really be okay?

347
00:21:18,586 --> 00:21:19,586
Seung Ri!

348
00:21:27,866 --> 00:21:28,866
Yeah.

349
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:33,019
There's no way Seung Ri would come
to a place we went to together.

350
00:21:55,446 --> 00:21:56,513
No way.

351
00:21:58,266 --> 00:21:59,733
My dad's a murderer?

352
00:22:02,546 --> 00:22:05,653
Dad, that's not true, right?

353
00:22:07,166 --> 00:22:08,166
Right?

354
00:22:09,633 --> 00:22:10,633
Seo Seung Ri.

355
00:22:20,980 --> 00:22:22,159
It really is you.

356
00:22:22,980 --> 00:22:25,386
What are you doing here all by yourself?
Do you know how worried I was?

357
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:27,533
Min Ho.

358
00:22:29,853 --> 00:22:32,593
Have you been drinking?
Why? What happened?

359
00:22:33,666 --> 00:22:34,993
It's you again.

360
00:22:36,726 --> 00:22:40,086
Whenever something happens,

361
00:22:40,626 --> 00:22:42,212
you always show up.

362
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:45,273
Seo Seung Ri's very own guardian angel.

363
00:22:52,560 --> 00:22:53,979
You're really drunk, aren't you?

364
00:22:54,146 --> 00:22:56,399
You're actually joking around with me.

365
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:05,173
Seung Ri, what's wrong?

366
00:23:06,793 --> 00:23:09,599
Talk to me. How am I supposed to know
if you don't say anything?

367
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:13,360
I just...

368
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:18,873
wanted to disappear somewhere,

369
00:23:23,193 --> 00:23:27,226
but I couldn't figure out where to go.

370
00:23:28,286 --> 00:23:30,539
Why? Is it because of Gyeol?

371
00:23:35,306 --> 00:23:37,073
Stop drinking. You're drunk.

372
00:23:39,159 --> 00:23:40,866
Come on. I'll take you home.

373
00:23:42,946 --> 00:23:45,999
Home? No, I don't want to go home.

374
00:23:46,586 --> 00:23:47,586
What?

375
00:23:49,486 --> 00:23:50,686
I can't go home.

376
00:23:52,433 --> 00:23:53,600
I just can't.

377
00:23:54,399 --> 00:23:55,826
What are you talking about?

378
00:23:56,212 --> 00:23:57,619
You're drunk. You need to go home.

379
00:23:58,139 --> 00:23:59,139
Come on.

380
00:24:12,919 --> 00:24:13,919
Seung Ri.

381
00:24:16,626 --> 00:24:17,626
I'm sorry.

382
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:20,700
Just...

383
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:24,200
let me stay like this for a little while.

384
00:24:30,373 --> 00:24:32,792
Okay. Do that.

385
00:24:47,113 --> 00:24:48,579
Are you really sure about this?

386
00:24:48,886 --> 00:24:50,453
You haven't driven much
since getting your license.

387
00:24:50,993 --> 00:24:52,506
Dad, you worry too much.

388
00:24:52,686 --> 00:24:55,606
A scooter and a car both run on wheels,
don't they?

389
00:24:55,886 --> 00:24:57,646
You haven't driven for that long?

390
00:24:58,933 --> 00:25:00,199
Why? Are you scared?

391
00:25:00,493 --> 00:25:01,679
Then you drive.

392
00:25:02,406 --> 00:25:04,712
I told you, I don't have a license.

393
00:25:05,213 --> 00:25:07,686
Seriously. No car and no license.

394
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,120
So what do you have?

395
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:10,560
My devastating good looks?

396
00:25:12,453 --> 00:25:13,453
We'll be back.

397
00:25:16,846 --> 00:25:18,878
Dad, how's Mom feeling?

398
00:25:18,879 --> 00:25:22,332
Your mom overdid it yesterday and seems
to have come down with something.

399
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:26,099
Whenever she's troubled,
she always pushes herself too hard.

400
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:29,505
I'll make her some porridge
and take care of her, so don't worry.

401
00:25:29,505 --> 00:25:31,051
- We'll be back.
- See you later.

402
00:25:31,186 --> 00:25:32,186
All right.

403
00:25:32,673 --> 00:25:34,426
- Drive safely.
- We will.

404
00:25:58,753 --> 00:25:59,753
Did you sleep well?

405
00:26:00,853 --> 00:26:02,419
Yes, Seung Ri.

406
00:26:03,273 --> 00:26:05,973
Get ready. Your family's probably worried.

407
00:26:23,246 --> 00:26:24,865
You said you knew how to drive.

408
00:26:24,866 --> 00:26:26,446
Is this what you call driving?

409
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:28,466
Don't talk to me.

410
00:26:29,286 --> 00:26:32,239
I was good during my road lessons
after getting my license.

411
00:26:33,112 --> 00:26:34,512
I guess it's been too long.

412
00:26:35,786 --> 00:26:37,406
- Seriously...
- Red light!

413
00:26:40,539 --> 00:26:42,473
Can we really make it
to the senior center like this?

414
00:26:42,773 --> 00:26:45,099
Let's pull over
and call a designated driver.

415
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:46,833
Once we get past here, it's a road I know.

416
00:26:47,106 --> 00:26:48,599
I'll be fine after that.

417
00:26:49,039 --> 00:26:52,239
Why are you such a scaredy-cat?

418
00:26:53,793 --> 00:26:55,426
The light's green. Here we go.

419
00:27:03,299 --> 00:27:04,719
What's wrong?

420
00:27:05,679 --> 00:27:08,093
You're making me even more nervous.

421
00:27:10,693 --> 00:27:12,826
Pull over. Hurry.

422
00:27:12,953 --> 00:27:16,046
Pull over? There's nowhere to stop here.

423
00:27:16,759 --> 00:27:19,239
Hurry. Pull over right there.

424
00:27:20,333 --> 00:27:21,820
What's wrong, Team Manager?

425
00:27:22,226 --> 00:27:23,226
What should I do?

426
00:27:24,079 --> 00:27:26,086
We're almost there.
Just hang on a little longer.

427
00:27:55,593 --> 00:27:57,726
Team Manager.

428
00:27:58,306 --> 00:28:00,172
Team Manager!

429
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:03,000
Team Manager!

430
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:09,000
(Our Happy Days)

431
00:28:09,533 --> 00:28:12,471
Do you have claustrophobia?

432
00:28:12,607 --> 00:28:13,939
Or maybe panic...

433
00:28:14,039 --> 00:28:16,006
Airport? Why are you
suddenly talking about an airport?

434
00:28:16,326 --> 00:28:18,359
Do you want to take a trip or something?

435
00:28:18,486 --> 00:28:20,105
I didn't make that decision lightly.

436
00:28:20,106 --> 00:28:22,331
I know how you felt.

437
00:28:22,332 --> 00:28:24,832
The moment I walk out of here,
I'm going to forget everything.

438
00:28:24,886 --> 00:28:26,373
How dare you come in here?

439
00:28:26,373 --> 00:28:29,340
I think I've found the solution
to our victory.

440
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:30,800
A solution?

441
00:28:30,800 --> 00:28:32,433
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
